comments.commentBody:
Here is a sure winner, well perhaps:

Opinion polls of self-identified DJT voters answering question that goes something like:

If it's a fact that the DJT campaign had conferred if not conspired with Russia regarding hacked intelligence information to do damage to Hillary's campaign:

Ought DJT apologize, resign, be impeached, and/or ignore molehill issue?

My wretched guess is that the bulk of DJT's voters will cuss nosey pollster, liberal media, and establishment.

Furthermore, Civil War II--red vs blue--ignites.

In other words, his voters will not be amused, and this d scandal continues
ad nausea infinitum, because the GOP won't dare cook its own goose.

It is amazing how the real question, what were all these people talking to the Russians about, isn't asked. It is unlikely that the same volume of communications went on with, say the French, German, or British ambassadors.
The highly effective truth manipulation squads have set the battlelines as, "prove anyone talked to anyone".
This no longer matters. It is time to find out what they were talking about. Sessions is a vicious, very bright, astute politician who aligned himself with Trump's skin head, racist, anti-semitic, nativist push. He lies?? It is amazing that this is taken as a surprise.
WHAT WERE THEY TALKING ABOUT?? Give them immunity, I don't care.

Gail is at her best when she stops being funny and starts getting real... You can smell the burn of the vitriol from here. Calling someone a pixie is about as funny as this one gets, and as far as namecaling goes, that is well within bounds.  One of your best this campaign season.  Brava!
Didn't he commit perjury?  Isn't that a felony?  What to do with Jeff Sessions? I think the answer is clear: charge him with perjury.
Lock him up! That's what we need to do.

"“He has these horrible views, but he’s sort of not vicious about them.”
One could say the same about Paul Ryan......."that one could smile, and smile, and be a villain."
As for Sessions, I'm becoming more, and more, dubious about his claim to have never met John Wilkes Booth.
And as for you, Ms. Collins, your ostensibly raised eyebrow about Pelosi's "far less" prompted a few of my eyebrows to raise, too.
If the old grey lady doesn't clutch her pearls, someone has to.

Sessions essentially perjured himself. Maybe you can argue semantics and he can weasel his way out of it, but everybody knows he didn't deal honestly with his colleagues in the Senate.  Their are no coincidences.  The only reason he recused himself, is he got caught with his hand in the Russian cookie jar.
Clevegas?
Cut a pixie some slack.  Jefferson Beauregard Sessions couldn't be less interested in a renewed Cold War.  He's still fighting the War of the Northern Agression.
Oh, that explains it. Thanks. Some of us had the idea that he might be a liar and perjurer.

“He has these horrible views, but he’s sort of not vicious about them.”

There's only one antidote when the bar is set this low, and Sessions isn't even the bottom of the new adminstration barrel: Netflix West Wing starting from season 1.

BENGHAZI! BENGHAZI! BENGHAZI!........(Russia? Feh.)  I guess as long as they repeal the ACA, outlaw gay marriage, deport a few million immigrants, the base won't give a gosh darn about the country formerly known as The Evil Empire.
"We"ll always have Cleveland"

Look, it's pretty simple. Sessions directly, of his own accord, stated that he did not have contact with the Russians during the campaign. He said NO. He did...TWICE. That's it, no wriggling out. He said No, even when that wasn't the question. He offered it. He lied...under oath! He's the Attorney General of the United States and he lied under oath. Unbelievable! I really don't care why he lied, what he did, who was there...he lied under oath. He has got to go. I guess when you are a racist eventually you get your due and he did. He might look like a sweet old guy but he's evil, albeit, not as evil as Bannon, but evil. He's got to go.

On a side note, people come on! All these Trump people talking to the Russians during and after the campaign, all of this while hacking was going on, and the GOP sees nothing wrong with this? And why are foreign ambassadors going to our conventions anyway. Yeah, yeah..."to show them what democracy looks like"..how's that working our for us? If I were a NYC detective, this case would be a no brainer. Follow the tracks to the answer. I have to say, the media has finally gotten their groove back, however late it is. NYTIMES, WaPost, CNN, MSNBC...keep it up. Be relentless. We will get through this and will be better and stronger. I'm even seeing some glimmers of hope in some on the other side. Or maybe they see the handwriting on the wall and are trying to buffer themselves. Either way, we will soon be on the road to fixing this...long road!
What to do with Jeff Sessions?  Keelhaul the guy, I say.

“He has these horrible views, but he’s sort of not vicious about them,” is one of the most pathetically funny statements that I've ever read-if not, THE most. This 'business' with Sessions and the Russians, at this point in time, is fundamentally irrelevant when compared to to the larger issue: Just plain Trump. I take the liberty of rewriting the above quoted line:Trump has sort of no views, but he's vicious about them."

Interesting, Trump makes a claim that Sweden has terrorist problems and oddly enough just a few days later, sure enough there is.

Go to YouTube: MILO Confronts the Panel | Overtime with Bill Maher (HBO) . Start at 10:50. Listen to Malcom Nance, US Counterterrorism Intelligence Officer explain the actual logistics and manpower needed to acquire information found on WikiLeaks.

In there also he tells how Trump would talk about something and some short time later it would happen. Everyone asked why did Trump dump on Sweden when there wasn't any evidence of is claims but yet to have it miraculously appear. He knew about what was going to happen beforehand. He is being fed the plot before it happens.

They need to get to the bottom of this cesspool  string of events and expose the liars and Rubel- Rousers so they don't undermine other democratic elections.  Democracy has been strapped to the stake and is slowing burning under this administration. If this is a witch hunt send me a broom. ( no offense meant to Wiccans)
"Follow the money".  Find a way to publish Trump's tax returns. Don't try to untie the Gordian knot; cut it.

John R. Beyrle, the United States ambassador to Moscow from 2008 to 2012, said he feared that “we’re beginning to out-Russian the Russians” by treating all contacts as suspicious.
All contacts aren't. And it isn't unreasonable that someone running for President - especially when they are a complete idiot - might want to have his surrogates speak with some foreign leaders in an effort to gain any understanding of "how this whole foreign policy thing works"!? (My quotes).
So did this many surrogates also meet with the ambassador from the Ukraine - maybe to hear out their side of the story?
And what about our other adversaries? Is there evidence of multiple meetings with the Chinese ambassador? The Iranian ambassador or UN rep? Anyone from North Korea? Where are the half dozen or more connections with people from all of those countries that suggest this is all just friendly chit chat?
Witch hunt, Trump says.  Is it time to start chanting "LOCK HIM UP!

Sorry but that yield calculation is way off.  Earning $200 on $15,000 for 90 days is an annual rate of 5.4%.  Chase is paying another 0.03% as the regular interest on accounts with a $15,000 balance for relationship savings plus accounts and 0.01% for standard plus and all regular savings accounts.  At best a customer who keeps $15,000 on deposit for a full year earns $4.50 in interest and, with the $200 bonus, an annual rate of 1.36%.

The graph in this article says it. Who was the President on those boring flat line? Maybe Trump should look at this graph since he despises single spaced six page report and prefers maps and graphs. Any tweet Mr. Trump?

Do you mean the one Alexander Hamilton founded?  Historians tend to feel it went well.  It was opposed by those who didn't understand finance like Hamilton did and it's charter expired at the end of 20 years.

Brandon Kaplowitz
The U.S. has the currency to which all the rest of the world's currencies use for comparison, and the interest rates will tend to be independent of the interests rates of other countries and so the exchange rates, too. So there will be an effect upon the cost of money internationally from the policies of the Fed, which might not be the case if the U.S. economy was very small.
